steps.desc: steps for each paramter, can either be the number or a list of step values

epsilon.desc: Step size to use in numerically evaluating gradient

factr.desc: ftol = factr*EPS, where EPS is machine precision (usually ~ 2e-16)

m.desc: Max number of corrections to define limited memory matrix

pgtol.desc: Gradient tolerance: if gradient_i > pgtol for all i, exit
